line_1: No Robber comes that preys on weaker Shoals.
line_2: No Whaly Monster here destructive rolls,

line_1: No curbing Law restrains the greedy Shoals,
line_2: No Sense of Wrong th' ungovern'd Wish controlls.

line_1: All give the Sea, and drive their mingled Shoals.
line_2: While o'er the Floods the wanton Dolphin rolls,

line_1: With Rage inveterate the restless Shoals
line_2: Make at his Head, and on his azure Jowls

line_1: And shining Mack'rell swim for us in Shoals.
line_2: The Cod (delicious Food!) Mullets and Soles,

line_1: Sending old rakes to church in shoals,
line_2: Like children sniv'ling for their souls,
